&gt;&gt; Dr. John Haskell:
Let me first welcome you

00:00:18.770 --> 00:00:20.840
to the Library, to the
Jefferson Building.

00:00:20.840 --> 00:00:23.110
I'm John Haskell, Director
of the Kluge Center.

00:00:23.110 --> 00:00:25.350
Our offices are right
through the doors over here.

00:00:25.350 --> 00:00:26.970
And we're so happy you came.

00:00:26.970 --> 00:00:31.110
I want to start by
introducing Yasmina Sioud.

00:00:31.110 --> 00:00:34.220
Who's the Deputy Head of
Press and Public Diplomacy

00:00:34.220 --> 00:00:35.520
for the Delegation

00:00:35.520 --> 00:00:37.240
of the European Union
to the United States.

00:00:37.240 --> 00:00:39.590
Yasmina? Right here.

00:00:39.590 --> 00:00:41.510
I was like where is she?

00:00:41.510 --> 00:00:46.870
[ Applause ]

00:00:46.870 --> 00:00:49.410
&gt;&gt; Yasmina Sioud:
Oops, can I move this?

00:00:49.410 --> 00:00:51.640
Well, good afternoon, everybody.

00:00:51.640 --> 00:00:54.550
I'm delighted to be at
the Kluge Center today

00:00:54.550 --> 00:00:58.310
to hear Kluge Fellow
Davide Ceriani.

00:00:58.310 --> 00:01:00.190
Good pronunciation.

00:01:00.190 --> 00:01:04.180
Presenting his research
on this fascinating topic.

00:01:04.180 --> 00:01:06.180
The growth of Italian-American
culture

00:01:06.180 --> 00:01:09.980
through opera until the 1940s.

00:01:09.980 --> 00:01:13.320
I myself was not a Kluge Fellow.

00:01:13.320 --> 00:01:16.300
But I also had the chance as
a master's student in the US

00:01:16.300 --> 00:01:19.540
to take advantage of
the Library of Congress.

00:01:19.540 --> 00:01:21.660
And its wealth of
documents and materials.

00:01:21.660 --> 00:01:25.990
So I, I know how
important this is.

00:01:25.990 --> 00:01:28.610
Today's program is a
signature event of the,

00:01:28.610 --> 00:01:31.120
of the European Month
of Culture.

00:01:31.120 --> 00:01:34.840
Resulting from a collaboration
between the Kluge Center,

00:01:34.840 --> 00:01:38.310
the Delegation of the European
Union, the Italian Embassy.

00:01:38.310 --> 00:01:41.310
And the Italian Cultural
Institute.

00:01:41.310 --> 00:01:44.260
As you may know, or
not, the European Month

00:01:44.260 --> 00:01:48.610
of Culture is organized every
year by the European Delegation.

00:01:48.610 --> 00:01:53.390
For the month of May and
for the past six years.

00:01:53.390 --> 00:01:55.030
And it offers a full month

00:01:55.030 --> 00:01:58.010
of cultural events
highlighting the diversity

00:01:58.010 --> 00:01:59.310
and the innovation.

00:01:59.310 --> 00:02:03.200
Cultures of all our 28
countries that are members

00:02:03.200 --> 00:02:05.260
of the European Union.

00:02:05.260 --> 00:02:09.170
This year we have close to 100
events in the Washington area.

00:02:09.170 --> 00:02:12.040
With participation of
all our 28 embassies

00:02:12.040 --> 00:02:16.530
and multiple US cultural and
educational institutions.

00:02:16.530 --> 00:02:21.030
So I would like here to extend
the EU delegation's deepest

00:02:21.030 --> 00:02:23.160
appreciation to the Kluge Center

00:02:23.160 --> 00:02:26.540
for what is now our
third-year collaboration.

00:02:26.540 --> 00:02:29.690
In this EU Month of Culture.

00:02:29.690 --> 00:02:32.070
So thank you, Dr.
Haskell, for your support.

00:02:32.070 --> 00:02:35.460
And for the excellent work
done by Travis Hensley.

00:02:35.460 --> 00:02:37.120
I don't know where he is.

00:02:37.120 --> 00:02:41.610
But we look forward to many
more years of collaboration.

00:02:41.610 --> 00:02:47.790
And I'll leave the floor to Dr.
Haskell for your conversation.

00:02:51.040 --> 00:02:53.060
&gt;&gt; Dr. John Haskell: Before
we get to our multimedia show

00:02:53.060 --> 00:02:56.790
which will be led by
Dr. Ceriani over here.

00:02:56.790 --> 00:03:01.000
Let me, let me just say a word
or two about the Kluge Center.

